#. <section class="sutta" id="mn142"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn142:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 142"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 142"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn142:0.2"
msgid "Dakkhiṇāvibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Analysis of Offerings to the Teacher"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.253"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn142:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. VAR: mahāpajāpati → mahāpajāpatī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn142:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī navaṃ dussayugaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Mahāpajāpati Gotamī approached the Buddha bringing a new pair of "
"garments. She bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn142:2.2"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, navaṃ dussayugaṃ bhagavantaṃ uddissa sāmaṃ kantaṃ sāmaṃ "
"vāyitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have spun and woven this new pair of garments specially for the "
"Buddha."

msgctxt "mn142:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ me, bhante, bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "May the Buddha please accept this from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "mn142:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When she said this, the Buddha said to her:"

msgctxt "mn142:2.5"
msgid "“saṃghe, gotami, dehi."
msgstr "“Give it to the Saṅgha, Gotamī."

msgctxt "mn142:2.6"
msgid "Saṃghe te dinne ahañceva pūjito bhavissāmi saṃgho cā”ti."
msgstr "When you give to the Saṅgha, both the Saṅgha and I will be honored.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:2.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "mn142:2.8"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, navaṃ dussayugaṃ bhagavantaṃ uddissa sāmaṃ kantaṃ sāmaṃ "
"vāyitaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn142:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ me, bhante, bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn142:2.10"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn142:2.11"
msgid "“saṅghe, gotami, dehi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn142:2.12"
msgid "Saṅghe te dinne ahañceva pūjito bhavissāmi saṅgho cā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:2.13"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time, Mahāpajāpatī Gotamī said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn142:2.14"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, navaṃ dussayugaṃ bhagavantaṃ uddissa sāmaṃ kantaṃ sāmaṃ "
"vāyitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have spun and woven this new pair of garments specially for the "
"Buddha."

msgctxt "mn142:2.15"
msgid "Taṃ me, bhante, bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "May the Buddha please accept this from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "mn142:2.16"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, the Buddha said to her:"

msgctxt "mn142:2.17"
msgid "“saṅghe, gotami, dehi."
msgstr "“Give it to the Saṅgha, Gotamī."

msgctxt "mn142:2.18"
msgid "Saṅghe te dinne ahañceva pūjito bhavissāmi saṅgho cā”ti."
msgstr "When you give to the Saṅgha, both the Saṅgha and I will be honored.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.254"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn142:3.2"
msgid ""
"“paṭiggaṇhātu, bhante, bhagavā mahāpajāpatiyā gotamiyā navaṃ dussayugaṃ."
msgstr "“Sir, please accept the new pair of garments from Mahāpajāpati Gotamī."

#. VAR: Bahūpakārā → bahukārā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn142:3.3"
msgid ""
"Bahūpakārā, bhante, mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavato mātucchā āpādikā posikā "
"khīrassa dāyikā;"
msgstr ""
"Sir, Mahāpajāpatī was very helpful to the Buddha. As his aunt, she raised "
"him, nurtured him, and gave him her milk."

msgctxt "mn142:3.4"
msgid "bhagavantaṃ janettiyā kālaṅkatāya thaññaṃ pāyesi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha’s birth mother passed away, she nurtured him at her own "
"breast."

msgctxt "mn142:3.5"
msgid "Bhagavāpi, bhante, bahūpakāro mahāpajāpatiyā gotamiyā."
msgstr "And the Buddha has been very helpful to Mahāpajāpatī."

msgctxt "mn142:3.6"
msgid ""
"Bhagavantaṃ, bhante, āgamma mahāpajāpati gotamī buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā, "
"dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā, saṃghaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā."
msgstr ""
"It is owing to the Buddha that Mahāpajāpatī has gone for refuge to the "
"Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:3.7"
msgid ""
"Bhagavantaṃ, bhante, āgamma mahāpajāpati gotamī pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā "
"adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā "
"surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā."
msgstr ""
"It’s owing to the Buddha that she refrains from killing living creatures, "
"stealing, committing sexual misconduct, lying, and taking alcoholic drinks "
"that cause negligence."

msgctxt "mn142:3.8"
msgid ""
"Bhagavantaṃ, bhante, āgamma mahāpajāpati gotamī buddhe aveccappasādena "
"samannāgatā, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgatā, saṃghe aveccappasādena "
"samannāgatā ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgatā."
msgstr ""
"It’s owing to the Buddha that she has experiential confidence in the Buddha, "
"the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and has the ethics loved by the noble ones."

msgctxt "mn142:3.9"
msgid ""
"Bhagavantaṃ, bhante, āgamma mahāpajāpati gotamī dukkhe nikkaṅkhā, "
"dukkhasamudaye nikkaṅkhā, dukkhanirodhe nikkaṅkhā, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā "
"paṭipadāya nikkaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s owing to the Buddha that she is free of doubt regarding suffering, its "
"origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation."

msgctxt "mn142:3.10"
msgid "Bhagavāpi, bhante, bahūpakāro mahāpajāpatiyā gotamiyā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha has been very helpful to Mahāpajāpatī.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:4.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, ānanda."
msgstr "“That’s so true, Ānanda."

msgctxt "mn142:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hānanda, puggalo puggalaṃ āgamma buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, dhammaṃ "
"saraṇaṃ gato hoti, saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, imassānanda, puggalassa iminā "
"puggalena na suppatikāraṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When someone has enabled you to go for refuge, it’s not easy to repay them"

msgctxt "mn142:4.3"
msgid ""
"abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammacīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappacc"
"ayabhesajjaparikkhārānuppadānena."
msgstr ""
"by bowing down to them, rising up for them, greeting them with joined palms, "
"and observing proper etiquette for them; or by providing them with robes, "
"alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hānanda, puggalo puggalaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā "
"paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, "
"surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, imassānanda, puggalassa iminā "
"puggalena na suppatikāraṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When someone has enabled you to refrain from killing, stealing, sexual "
"misconduct, lying, and alcoholic drinks that cause negligence, it’s not easy "
"to repay them …"

msgctxt "mn142:4.5"
msgid ""
"abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammacīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappacc"
"ayabhesajjaparikkhārānuppadānena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:4.6"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hānanda, puggalo puggalaṃ āgamma buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato "
"hoti, dhamme … saṅghe … ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti, imassānanda, "
"puggalassa iminā puggalena na suppatikāraṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When someone has enabled you to have experiential confidence in the Buddha, "
"the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and the ethics loved by the noble ones, it’s "
"not easy to repay them …"

msgctxt "mn142:4.7"
msgid ""
"abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammacīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappacc"
"ayabhesajjaparikkhārānuppadānena."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:4.8"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hānanda, puggalo puggalaṃ āgamma dukkhe nikkaṅkho hoti, dukkhasamudaye "
"nikkaṅkho hoti, dukkhanirodhe nikkaṅkho hoti, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā "
"paṭipadāya nikkaṅkho hoti, imassānanda, puggalassa iminā puggalena na "
"suppatikāraṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When someone has enabled you to be free of doubt regarding suffering, its "
"origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation, it’s "
"not easy to repay them"

msgctxt "mn142:4.9"
msgid ""
"abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammacīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappacc"
"ayabhesajjaparikkhārānuppadānena."
msgstr ""
"by bowing down to them, rising up for them, greeting them with joined palms, "
"and observing proper etiquette for them; or by providing them with robes, "
"alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.255"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:5.1"
msgid "Cuddasa kho panimānanda, pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "Ānanda, there are these fourteen personal offerings to a teacher."

msgctxt "mn142:5.2"
msgid "Katamā cuddasa?"
msgstr "What fourteen?"

msgctxt "mn142:5.3"
msgid "Tathāgate arahante sammāsambuddhe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened "
"Buddha."

msgctxt "mn142:5.4"
msgid "ayaṃ paṭhamā pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the first personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.5"
msgid "Paccekasambuddhe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to a Buddha awakened for themselves."

msgctxt "mn142:5.6"
msgid "ayaṃ dutiyā pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the second personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.7"
msgid "Tathāgatasāvake arahante dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to a perfected one."

msgctxt "mn142:5.8"
msgid "ayaṃ tatiyā pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the third personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.9"
msgid "Arahattaphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to a someone practicing to realize the fruit of perfection."

msgctxt "mn142:5.10"
msgid "ayaṃ catutthī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the fourth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.11"
msgid "Anāgāmissa dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to a non-returner."

msgctxt "mn142:5.12"
msgid "ayaṃ pañcamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the fifth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.13"
msgid "Anāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to a someone practicing to realize the fruit of non-return."

msgctxt "mn142:5.14"
msgid "ayaṃ chaṭṭhī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the sixth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.15"
msgid "Sakadāgāmissa dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to a once-returner."

msgctxt "mn142:5.16"
msgid "ayaṃ sattamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the seventh personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.17"
msgid "Sakadāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to a someone practicing to realize the fruit of once-return."

msgctxt "mn142:5.18"
msgid "ayaṃ aṭṭhamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the eighth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.19"
msgid "Sotāpanne dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to a stream-enterer."

msgctxt "mn142:5.20"
msgid "ayaṃ navamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the ninth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.21"
msgid "Sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to a someone practicing to realize the fruit of stream-"
"entry."

msgctxt "mn142:5.22"
msgid "ayaṃ dasamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the tenth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.23"
msgid "Bāhirake kāmesu vītarāge dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to someone outside of Buddhism who is free of sensual "
"desire."

msgctxt "mn142:5.24"
msgid "ayaṃ ekādasamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the eleventh personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.25"
msgid "Puthujjanasīlavante dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to an ordinary person who has good ethical conduct."

msgctxt "mn142:5.26"
msgid "ayaṃ dvādasamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the twelfth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.27"
msgid "Puthujjanadussīle dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to an ordinary person who has bad ethical conduct."

msgctxt "mn142:5.28"
msgid "ayaṃ terasamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the thirteenth personal teacher’s offering."

msgctxt "mn142:5.29"
msgid "Tiracchānagate dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to an animal."

msgctxt "mn142:5.30"
msgid "ayaṃ cuddasamī pāṭipuggalikā dakkhiṇāti."
msgstr "This is the fourteenth personal teacher’s offering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, tiracchānagate dānaṃ datvā sataguṇā dakkhiṇā pāṭikaṅkhitabbā, "
"puthujjanadussīle dānaṃ datvā sahassaguṇā dakkhiṇā pāṭikaṅkhitabbā, "
"puthujjanasīlavante dānaṃ datvā satasahassaguṇā dakkhiṇā pāṭikaṅkhitabbā, "
"bāhirake kāmesu vītarāge dānaṃ datvā koṭisatasahassaguṇā dakkhiṇā "
"pāṭikaṅkhitabbā, sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne dānaṃ datvā "
"asaṅkheyyā appameyyā dakkhiṇā pāṭikaṅkhitabbā, ko pana vādo sotāpanne, ko "
"pana vādo sakadāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne, ko pana vādo "
"sakadāgāmissa, ko pana vādo anāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne, ko pana "
"vādo anāgāmissa, ko pana vādo arahattaphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanne, ko pana "
"vādo arahante, ko pana vādo paccekasambuddhe, ko pana vādo tathāgate "
"arahante sammāsambuddhe."
msgstr ""
"Now, Ānanda, gifts to the following persons may be expected to yield the "
"following returns. To an animal, a hundred times. To an unethical ordinary "
"person, a thousand. To an ethical ordinary person, a hundred thousand. To an "
"outsider free of sensual desire, 10,000,000,000. But a gift to someone "
"practicing to realize the fruit of stream-entry may be expected to yield "
"incalculable, immeasurable returns. How much more so a gift to a stream-"
"enterer, someone practicing to realize the fruit of once-return, a once-"
"returner, someone practicing to realize the fruit of non-return, a non-"
"returner, someone practicing to realize the fruit of perfection, a perfected "
"one, or a Buddha awakened for themselves? How much more so a Realized One, a "
"perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.256"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:7.1"
msgid "Satta kho panimānanda, saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "But there are, Ānanda, seven teacher’s offerings bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.2"
msgid "Katamā satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "mn142:7.3"
msgid "Buddhappamukhe ubhatosaṅghe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to the Saṅgha of both monks and nuns headed by the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.4"
msgid "ayaṃ paṭhamā saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the first teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.5"
msgid "Tathāgate parinibbute ubhatosaṅghe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift to the Saṅgha of both monks and nuns after the Buddha has "
"finally become extinguished."

msgctxt "mn142:7.6"
msgid "ayaṃ dutiyā saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the second teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.7"
msgid "Bhikkhusaṅghe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to the Saṅgha of monks."

msgctxt "mn142:7.8"
msgid "ayaṃ tatiyā saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the third teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.9"
msgid "Bhikkhunisaṅghe dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr "One gives a gift to the Saṅgha of nuns."

msgctxt "mn142:7.10"
msgid "ayaṃ catutthī saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the fourth teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.11"
msgid "‘Ettakā me bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca saṅghato uddissathā’ti dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift, thinking: ‘Appoint this many monks and nuns for me from "
"the Saṅgha.’"

msgctxt "mn142:7.12"
msgid "ayaṃ pañcamī saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the fifth teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.13"
msgid "‘Ettakā me bhikkhū saṅghato uddissathā’ti dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift, thinking: ‘Appoint this many monks for me from the Saṅgha.’"

msgctxt "mn142:7.14"
msgid "ayaṃ chaṭṭhī saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the sixth teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:7.15"
msgid "‘Ettakā me bhikkhuniyo saṅghato uddissathā’ti dānaṃ deti—"
msgstr ""
"One gives a gift, thinking: ‘Appoint this many nuns for me from the Saṅgha.’"

msgctxt "mn142:7.16"
msgid "ayaṃ sattamī saṅghagatā dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "This is the seventh teacher’s offering bestowed on a Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:8.1"
msgid ""
"Bhavissanti kho panānanda, anāgatamaddhānaṃ gotrabhuno kāsāvakaṇṭhā dussīlā "
"pāpadhammā."
msgstr ""
"In times to come there will be members of the spiritual family merely by "
"virtue of wearing ocher cloth around their necks; but they are unethical and "
"of bad character."

msgctxt "mn142:8.2"
msgid "Tesu dussīlesu saṅghaṃ uddissa dānaṃ dassanti."
msgstr ""
"People will give gifts to those unethical people in the name of the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn142:8.3"
msgid "Tadāpāhaṃ, ānanda, saṅghagataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ asaṅkheyyaṃ appameyyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Even then, I say, a teacher’s offering bestowed on the Saṅgha is "
"incalculable and immeasurable."

msgctxt "mn142:8.4"
msgid ""
"Na tvevāhaṃ, ānanda, kenaci pariyāyena saṅghagatāya dakkhiṇāya "
"pāṭipuggalikaṃ dānaṃ mahapphalataraṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"But I say that there is no way a personal offering can be more fruitful than "
"one bestowed on a Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:9.1"
msgid "Catasso kho imā, ānanda, dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, there are these four ways of purifying an offering to a teacher."

msgctxt "mn142:9.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn142:9.3"
msgid "Atthānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato."
msgstr ""
"There’s an offering to a teacher that’s purified by the giver, not the "
"recipient."

msgctxt "mn142:9.4"
msgid "Atthānanda, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati no dāyakato."
msgstr ""
"There’s an offering to a teacher that’s purified by the recipient, not the "
"giver."

msgctxt "mn142:9.5"
msgid "Atthānanda, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato."
msgstr ""
"There’s an offering to a teacher that’s purified by neither the giver nor "
"the recipient."

msgctxt "mn142:9.6"
msgid "Atthānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca."
msgstr ""
"There’s an offering to a teacher that’s purified by both the giver and the "
"recipient."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:10.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato?"
msgstr ""
"And how is an offering to a teacher purified by the giver, not the recipient?"

msgctxt "mn142:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, dāyako hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo, paṭiggāhakā honti dussīlā "
"pāpadhammā—"
msgstr ""
"It’s when the giver is ethical, of good character, but the recipient is "
"unethical, of bad character."

msgctxt "mn142:10.3"
msgid "evaṃ kho, ānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:11.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati no dāyakato?"
msgstr ""
"And how is an offering to a teacher purified by the recipient, not the giver?"

#. VAR: sīlavanto → sīlavantā (si)
msgctxt "mn142:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, dāyako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo, paṭiggāhakā honti sīlavanto "
"kalyāṇadhammā—"
msgstr ""
"It’s when the giver is unethical, of bad character, but the recipient is "
"ethical, of good character."

msgctxt "mn142:11.3"
msgid "evaṃ kho, ānanda, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati no dāyakato."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:12.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato?"
msgstr ""
"And how is an offering to a teacher purified by neither the giver nor the "
"recipient?"

msgctxt "mn142:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, dāyako ca hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo, paṭiggāhakā ca honti dussīlā "
"pāpadhammā—"
msgstr ""
"It’s when both the giver and the recipient are unethical, of bad character."

msgctxt "mn142:12.3"
msgid "evaṃ kho, ānanda, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati no paṭiggāhakato."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.257"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:13.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca?"
msgstr ""
"And how is an offering to a teacher purified by both the giver and the "
"recipient?"

msgctxt "mn142:13.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, dāyako ca hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo, paṭiggāhakā ca honti "
"sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā—"
msgstr ""
"It’s when both the giver and the recipient are ethical, of good character."

msgctxt "mn142:13.3"
msgid "evaṃ kho, ānanda, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn142:13.4"
msgid "Imā kho, ānanda, catasso dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo”ti."
msgstr "These are the four ways of purifying an offering to a teacher.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn142:14.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.3"
msgid "“Yo sīlavā dussīlesu dadāti dānaṃ,"
msgstr "“When an ethical person with trusting heart"

#. <br>
#. VAR: laddhaṃ → laddhā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn142:14.4"
msgid "Dhammena laddhaṃ supasannacitto;"
msgstr "gives a proper gift to unethical persons,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.5"
msgid "Abhisaddahaṃ kammaphalaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "trusting in the ample fruit of deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.6"
msgid "Sā dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati."
msgstr "that offering is purified by the giver."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.7"
msgid "Yo dussīlo sīlavantesu dadāti dānaṃ,"
msgstr "When an unethical and untrusting person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.8"
msgid "Adhammena laddhaṃ appasannacitto;"
msgstr "gives an improper gift to ethical persons,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.9"
msgid "Anabhisaddahaṃ kammaphalaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "not trusting in the ample fruit of deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.10"
msgid "Sā dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati."
msgstr "that offering is purified by the receivers."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.11"
msgid "Yo dussīlo dussīlesu dadāti dānaṃ,"
msgstr "When an unethical and untrusting person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.12"
msgid "Adhammena laddhaṃ appasannacitto;"
msgstr "gives an improper gift to ethical persons,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.13"
msgid "Anabhisaddahaṃ kammaphalaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "not trusting in the ample fruit of deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.14"
msgid "Na taṃ dānaṃ vipulapphalanti brūmi."
msgstr "I declare that gift is not very fruitful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.15"
msgid "Yo sīlavā sīlavantesu dadāti dānaṃ,"
msgstr "When an ethical person with trusting heart"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.16"
msgid "Dhammena laddhaṃ supasannacitto;"
msgstr "gives a proper gift to ethical persons,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.17"
msgid "Abhisaddahaṃ kammaphalaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "trusting in the ample fruit of deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.18"
msgid "Taṃ ve dānaṃ vipulapphalanti brūmi."
msgstr "I declare that gift is abundantly fruitful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.19"
msgid "Yo vītarāgo vītarāgesu dadāti dānaṃ,"
msgstr "But when the passionless gives to the passionless"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.20"
msgid "Dhammena laddhaṃ supasannacitto;"
msgstr "a proper gift with trusting heart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.21"
msgid "Abhisaddahaṃ kammaphalaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "trusting in the ample fruit of deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.22"
msgid "Taṃ ve dānaṃ āmisadānānamaggan”ti."
msgstr "that’s truly the best of material gifts.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn142:14.23"
msgid "Dakkhiṇāvibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn142:14.24"
msgid "Vibhaṅgavaggo niṭṭhito catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn142:14.25"
msgid "Bhaddekānandakaccāna,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.26"
msgid "Lomasakaṅgiyāsubho;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.27"
msgid "Mahākammasaḷāyatanavibhaṅgā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn142:14.28"
msgid "Uddesaaraṇā dhātu saccaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn142:14.29"
msgid "Dakkhiṇāvibhaṅgasuttanti."
msgstr ""
